<subSubSection pageNumber="732" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="732">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Note:</emphasis>
Fawcett &amp; Rendle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
3: 158. 1914) stated &quot;type in Herb. Linn.&quot;, evidently intending sheet 472.1 (LINN), and this choice has been followed by authors such as Nowicke (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">Ann. Missouri Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
55: 344. 1969) and Ghosh &amp; Sikdar (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">J. Econ. Taxon. Bot.</emphasis>
4: 155. 1983). However, the sheet lacks a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="732">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“1”">&quot;1&quot;</normalizedToken>
), written by Linnaeus, and is a post-1753 addition to the collection and so not original material for the name. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Barrie’s">Barrie's</normalizedToken>
1993 choice is therefore accepted here.
</paragraph>
